# Design System Conventions

> **Start here:** Read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for the full architectural context —
> design principles, layer model, token system, prefix mechanics, Figma integration,
> build chain, and decision log.

You are working in a multi-framework design system monorepo. All components are built for React, Vue, and Svelte with shared design tokens and a **CSS-first base layer**.

## CSS-First Architecture — CRITICAL

- ALL visual styles live in `packages/css-components/` as BEM SCSS
- Framework components are THIN WRAPPERS — they map props to BEM class names
- Framework components MUST NOT define their own `<style>` blocks or CSS Modules
- BEM naming: `.{prefix}-{component}`, `.{prefix}-{component}--{variant}`, `.{prefix}-{component}__{element}`

## Token Usage — CRITICAL

- NEVER use hardcoded color, spacing, or typography values
- ALWAYS use CSS custom properties: `var(--vcds-{category}-{name})`
- Components use SEMANTIC tokens, never primitive tokens
- Examples: `var(--vcds-color-action-primary)`, `var(--vcds-spacing-md)`, `var(--vcds-font-size-body)`

## Component Rules

- Every component must be accessible (WCAG 2.2 AA)
- Include keyboard navigation and ARIA attributes
- Export TypeScript types for all props
- Write unit tests with axe-core a11y checks
- Create Storybook stories for all variants

## Decision Capture

Read `DECISIONS.md` before starting any task. Apply every documented decision to your output. After completing a task that established a new repeatable pattern (variant naming, token scale, accessibility convention, etc.), suggest the user document it in `DECISIONS.md` so it's applied consistently going forward.

## When Creating a Component — Order matters:

1. Check `/blueprints/scss/` for the SCSS template (start here)
2. Create SCSS in `packages/css-components/src/components/`
3. Create HTML reference in `packages/html/examples/`
4. Check `/blueprints/{framework}/` for the wrapper template
5. Create thin wrappers in React, Vue, Svelte (props → BEM classes)
6. Check `/a11y/checklists/component.md` for accessibility requirements
7. Add Storybook stories in `packages/docs/stories/`
